title: Catalan pro-independence mayors defy Spanish government before referendum
description:
More than 700 mayors from across the Catalonia region of northeast Spain have protested in Barcelona in support of a planned independence referendum.

Political tensions in Spain are increasing as the proposed October voting date nears.

The Catalan government plans to go ahead with the referendum despite the central government's warning of legal prosecution.

Al Jazeera's Karl Penhaul reports from Barcelona.
